original_problem:
A stem-and-leaf plot shows the number of seconds taken by 9 students to complete a puzzle. In the stem-and-leaf plot, $2 \ 5$ represents 25 seconds. What is the median of this data set? Express your answer in seconds.

\begin{tabular}{c|ccccc}
0&5&8&9&&\\
1&2&4&&&\\
2&5&6&7&&\\
\end{tabular}

What is the probability of spinning the spinner pictured and getting an even number? Express your answer as a common fraction. [asy]
import olympiad; defaultpen(linewidth(0.8)); size(100); dotfactor=4;
draw(Circle((0,0),1));
string[] labels = {"2","4","6","8","10","12"};
for(int i = 0; i < 6; ++i){

label(labels[i],0.7*dir(60*i));

draw((0,0)--dir(60*i - 30));
}
draw((0,0)--0.7*dir(130),linewidth(2.0),EndArrow(size=6));
[/asy]

In this Number Wall, you add the numbers next to each other and write the sum in the block directly above the two numbers. Which number will be the block labeled '$n$'? [asy]
draw((0,0)--(6,0)--(6,2)--(0,2)--cycle);
draw((2,0)--(2,2));
draw((4,0)--(4,2));
draw((1,2)--(5,2)--(5,4)--(1,4)--cycle);
draw((3,2)--(3,4));
draw((2,4)--(2,6)--(4,6)--(4,4));
label("$n$",(1,1));
label("2",(3,1));
label("3",(5,1));
label("?",(2,3));
label("10",(3,5));
[/asy]

solution:
1. **Determine the length of the rectangle**:
   \[
   \text{Length} = \frac{24}{4} = 6 \text{ units}
   \]
2. **Calculate the perimeter of the rectangle**:
   \[
   \text{Perimeter} = 2 \times (6 + 4) = 2 \times 10 = 20 \text{ units}
   \]

**Final Answer**:
\boxed{20}

